python hf_image_text_multi_cls_multiproc.py --from_pretrained THUDM/cogagent-chat-hf --bf16 --image_dir ../irfl_data/raw_data/image_data --text_file ../irfl_data/intermediate_data/idiom_image_text_pairs.txt --save_file ../irfl_data/intermediate_data/idiom_vision_text_label_logits.jsonl --query "Given an image and an idiom, categorize the relationship between them based on how the image depicts the idiom's meaning. Consider the following categories: \n\nA: Partial Literal - Some elements of the idiom are visualized in the image. \nB: Figurative - The image captures one or more metaphorical definitions of the idiom without directly illustrating the words. \nC: Figurative Literal - The image combines elements of both the 'Figurative' and 'Literal'/'Partial Literal' interpretations, showing a metaphorical understanding and some literal elements of the idiom. \nD: Literal - The image directly illustrates the idiom as it is stated, with all elements clearly depicted. \nE: None - The image does not fit any of the above categories. \n\nAssess how the image conveys the idiom's meaning and choose the most fitting categorization. Here is the idom: " --cache_dir data/user_data/zqi2 --options "['A','B','C','D','E']" --num_processes 4